data.description: This absolutely beautiful Colorado property with a one-level home with captivating panoramic views of lush meadows and picturesque valleys. This very nice property is situated on horse-friendly grounds, and the surrounding pasture for grazing makes this home ideal for livestock. The home has a metal roof, the vents were replaced 2-3 years ago. The septic was serviced 3 years ago. Noteworthy features include spring-fed well water, which pumps consistently on demand; there is no cistern to hold the water. A new pressure pump for the well was installed in July 2023. Recently updated exterior and interior paint, and a convenient location only 20 minutes from the historic city of Cripple Creek. For a unique bonus, this property includes a mining claim, an exciting nod to the region's gold-rich history. So, as they say, there's still gold in them their hills! Your tranquil lifestyle begins here—contact us today to experience it for yourself. Buyers' due diligence is suggested for surrounding parcels.
